Georgia 332 km<br>
Iran (south) 432 km<br>
Iran (southwest) 179 km<br>
Russia 284 km<br>
Turkey 9 km<br>
<p>
Population:<br>
7.3 million<br>
54% urban<br>
89 persons/sq. km<br>
<p>
Ethnic composition:<br>
71% Azerbaijani<br>
11% Talish<br>
6% Russian<br>
4% Lezgi=20<br>
3% Daghestani<br>
3% Kurdish<br>
2% Avar<br>
<p>
The autonomous republic of Nakhichevan (pop. 350,000; 5,500 sq. km)=20<br>
as placed under Azerbaijani administration in 1921.=09<br>
<p>
Leadership:  Geidar Aliyev, President; Artur Rasizade, Prime=20<br>
Minister; Hasan Hasanov, Foreign Minister; Shamshaddin Khanbabayev,=20<br>
Premier of Nakhichevan.<br>
<p>
Independence:  Azerbaijan established its independence on August=20<br>
30, 1991.<br>
<p>
CIS membership status:  Azerbaijan joined the CIS on September 24,=20<br>
1993.<br>
<p>
Constitution:  A new constitution was passed by referendum in=20<br>
November 1995.<br>
<p>
Elections: Parliamentary elections for a new 125-seat legislature=20<br>
were held November 1995.<br>
<p>
Diplomatic representation:  The United States representative to=20<br>
Azerbaijan is Ambassador Richard Kauzlarich.  The Azerbaijani=20<br>
representative to the United States is Ambassador Hafiz Pashayev. =20<br>
The Azerbaijani representative to the United Nations is Eldar=20<br>
Guliyev.<br>
