                     MASS MEDIA: PRINCIPLES AND REALITY
            Monthly bulletin of Union of Journalist of Azerbaijan
                          N 9 (13)  September`1996


"...BUNIADOV ST.,BAKU"

   "Since now Vtoraya Sverdlovskaya steet in the capital of Azerbaijan Republic
is named after Adil Bunyadov". That was thr decision of the Architecture and
Urban Planning department of the Executive Committee of Baku City.
   A.Bunyadov started his work from  information agency  "Turan", and then
worked for Reuter. On 17 August, 1995 he was killed during recording the
Azerbaijan Army's capture of the Azerbaijan police special purpose unit's
headquarters.

REFUGEES ARE HUNGRY FOR INFORMATION AS WELL

   The head of refugee camp number 1 Jaffar Jabrailov appealed to the executives of
the national information services and international help organisations.He said
that since setting the camp no newspapers or magazines had been dilevered. and
he asked executives to arrange the dilevery of every single piece of
information to the camp.


" DEUTCH WAVE" BY THE CASPIAN SHORE"

    According to the agreement reached by the Azerbaijan National Televisiion and
Radio Company  and German "Deutch Wave"  some programs of the "Deutch wave"
will be broadcated to Azerbaijan. The  head of Russian Language department in
"Deutch wave" Mr. M.Zorichin is to visit our country.
    The "Deutch Wave" programs are broadcasted from a multistore building in a
suburb of Keln. Recently, great changes have taken place there. Regarding the
changes Mr. Diter Vairikh  answered some of our questions
D.V."In a short period of time we have adopted the latest technology achievmnets
in information and media sector. Now, the modern equipment is used. This is the
reason of an advance in our work. In the past we could broadcast only on
short waves, but now we are using satellite services. In the present,the number
of the progams, broadcasted on short waves has reached 39. Whereas, 20 per
cent of our listeners are being served using the satellite communication services.
This kind of service is employed only by us and CNN . A large number of changes
took place in "Deutch Wave" television company as well. The programs now are
broadcasted 24 hours a day. Most of them are broadcated in German(12 hours),
some - in English (10 hours), and only a little - in Spanish (2 hours).
The quality has improved as well.

    Q.What are you planning to change in broadcasting to the C.I.S. ?
    D.V.The former Soviet Union always listened to us as to a voice of free world.
But since the economic reforms started there, we have been trying to propogand
the democratic reforms. At the moment, programs in Russian are broadcasted 6
hours a day. And a flow of listeners' letters proves the fact  that the interest
in our programs continues to grow. Telemagazine "Western Europe" to about 70 local
tele and radio companies. For now because of financial problems  we can not
connect the C.I.S.to the cabel network.
   Q. How do you plan to improve the relations with the C.I.S. countries?
   D.V. We will  work in diferent directions. First, we should try to have  all
European programs, not only ours, to be retransmissed by the C.I.S.
telecompanies. Second, we will employ the people interested in German.The
number of such kind of people is amounted to 10 million. Last, we will increase
the number of programs on economic issues. More joint programs are planned.
Moreover,we will use the video tapes to improve the economic knowledge of our
employees.
   Q.Do you mean the seminars by corespondence?
   D.V.No , not at all. In order to increase the professionalism of our journalists
we have educational units in Berlin and Keln. Many C.I.S and East European
jounalists are invited every year


THE MEDIA IN AZERBAIJANI LANGUAGE IN GEORGIA

    In the present, one can find media editions in various, apart from Georgian,
languages: Russian, Azerbaijani, Armenian, Abkhazian, Osetian, German, Greek,
Kurdian and Hebrew.Most of the present publications has been published since
1920s. Due to the collapse of the U.S.S.R. and formation of independent Georgia
completely new newspapers started their publication. Among them there are the
papers of different societies, parties and organisations. In this article we
will try to elicudate the newspapers published in Azerbaijani language.

    Azeris

    According to the population survey, carried out in 1989, azeri population in
Georgia was nearly 1 mln people. They mostly concentrated in the south-east
Georgia (Dmanisi, Bolnisi, Marneuli, Gardabani districts}. Some of them live in
the capital - Tbilisi City, and others- in the main industrial cities like
Sagajero and Rustavi. They are mostly employed in agricultural sector and are
one of the major suppliers of agricultural goods to Tbilisi and Rustavi.
    Azeri residints of Georgia managed to hold on to their national traditions and
customs. There are many schools in south-eastern Georgia where  education is
given in Azerbaijani language. There is the Azerbaijani lanaguge school in the
Tbilisi Pedagogical University. One of the most popular organisations in Georgia
is Cultural and Charity centre " Birlick"  on behalf of which  paper "Gurjustan"
is publisheed

    Periodicals

    "Gurjustan"
    The newspaper was found in 1921,First it was called " Yeni Fikir" and
then "Soviet Gurjustan". At the moment, it comes out once a week  with the total
edition of 1000. The A-3 formated 4-page paper is totally financed from
the local budget and  has its rask to interprete the chronics of the events
taking place in the country's political and social life.
    The method of linotype is still used. Modern equipment has been
ordered from Baku but has not been delivered yet, the paper' journalists
said.
    Being unable to pay for the sevices of the state press disrtibutor "Matsne"
the paper's management is responsable for its distribution. All they can do is
to supply every single edition of the paper to the local press kiosks
    A huge attention is given to agricultural issues. That is why among people the
paper is called " Agricultural encyclopedia". Nowadays the readers are more
interested in  legislation on land than in weather forecasts, the papers editor
said.
    "Gurjustan" is also keen to teach its readers Georgian because the Georgian
language was not taught in Azerbaijani schools.
    Recently the paper started to publish the articles on religious  and
multinational issues Freuquently the materials on Nagorny Karabakh are
published.
   Due to the financial problems the wages of the paper's emloyees are very low.
The chief editor gets $12 a month

   " Marneuli "

   "Marneuli", a paper of the Local Executives organs  is published once a week.
The articles in Azerbaijani are placed on one of its pages. They are mostly the
translation of the rest of materials in the paper published in Georgian.

   Papers published in Azerbaijani before the collapse of the S.U. are:
   "Sangori"            Gardabani
   "Gelebe Bayragi"     Bolnisi
   "Trialeti"           Dmanisi
   They stopped their publishing in 1990.

   The Azeris, emmigrated from Georgia to Azerbaijan,  united in different
societies( "Borjali", "Garachop" and others) The objective of these societies
was to help its members  to settle down in Baku  and   they published a number
of papers and magazines ("Sabah", "Borjali" and others). However, the financial
problems and changes in socio-political situation in the country made them to
stop their activity

   Radio

   Every day for half an hour ( 19.30 - 20.00) the Georgian National Radio company
broadcasts  programs in Azerbaijani language. These programs tell its listners
about the socio-political events, taking place in the country and about culture
news.After what teh various entertaining programs are on the air.
   In opinion of local residents, the most comfortable mean to get a great deal of
information is the radio. The reason for that is a shortage in electroenergy and
the fact that the country population is unable to watch television.

    The media services in Armenian language in Georgia

    Armenian residents in Georgia can get education in Armenian as well as Azeri can.
There are 256 Armenian schools in Georgia.Moreover there is  the Armenian
language department in the Tbilisi Pedagogical Unversity and the Armneian Opera
Theatre in Tbilisi. Armenians mostly live in Samtskhe-Javakheti district and
thier total population in Georgia is amounted to 300,000.

    Newspaper "Erastan"
    It was found in 1921. Till recent years it was called "Sovetackan Erastan".It is
financed from the local budget and is published once a week with the total
edition of 200,000. The price  for A-3 formated 8-page edition is $0.2. in its
publishing the modern equipment, provided by  the International Armenian Charity
Organisation and the Armenian President's apparat, is used.
    Apart from "Erastan", the papers of Akhalkalaki, Akhaltsikhe and Ninotcmind
districts contain one page of articles in Armenian language.
Every day for half an hour the Georgian radio broadcasts programs in Armenian


NEWS

* Soon the first volume of complete collection of magazine " Molla Nasreddin"
is to come out of publishing. Nine volume of this collection is planned to be
printed in latin letters in Turkey

* September,2. Newspaper "Azadlig" was converted into a daily . The paper's
Deputy Editor Mr. S. Housseinli said, for a month time it was planned to publish
8-pages eddition on even weekdays and 4-page edition on odd weekdays. And then
starting from October it will be published in 8-page edition every day with a
total edition of 10,000 .This paper was created by the Azerbaijan People's
Front Party in 1989 and initially was coming out once a week

* Publishing House "Azerbaiajn" made an announcement: the fact that on 29 June,
1995,The National Bank  cessation of the checques collection  service led to an
increase of the amount owed by different papers to the House, which in its turn
was the reason of the worsening of the financial conditions of the House.
Therefore,the House demanded from its partners to settle the outstandig amounts
within a month time according to  closes 2.1.4 of the Contract between the House
and newspapers.

* Cnference on 160 anniversary of Hasan bey Zardabi was held in Zardab.

* THe press distributor " Gasid" infornmed during June and August only seven
newspapers were  subscribed. Their list is below:
 1.Azerbaijan                 1364
 2.Mubariz Keshikde           1252
 3.Azerbaijan muallimi        1211
 4.Vishka                     1167
 5.Bakinskiy rabochiy         934
 6.Halg gaseti                557
 7. Azerbaijan( in russian )  391

Note, the publishing houses "Azadlig","Millet", " Gunay", "Hurriat" and others
onuse the services of paper kiosk.

* The Executive Committee of Azerbaiajani Red Cresent Society  informed  that
new media service of the Society will periodically organise press-conferences
and briefings.

* The press ditributor "Gaya" informed that in June paper "Avrasia" sold by the
company was a best-seller. 23,000 copies were sold. The  second and third places
are of "Azadlig" (8,000) and "Super-market" (7,200) respectivevily. Figures on
some other papers are below:
Ayna-Zerkalo   5,219
Birja          1800
7 Gun          3300
In other words the company has realised 90 percent of its plans.  35 from
117 sold by the company  are published outside the country.

* The Press and Information Ministry of Nakhchivan Republic informed that it
intends to create the Publishing House

* Israeli Ambassador Plenipolentary in Azerbaijan Mr. E. Yotvat finiishing his
mission in Azerbaijan  invited jounalists to his farewell meeting.In organised
by the journalists' society " Yeni Nesil" event, the Ambassador stressing the
journalists' big role in Azerbaijan's further development thanked them very much.

* A group of famous journalists addressed  President H.Aliyev with an appeal
to help AzTV reporter A. Asadov to make all necessary decorative works in his
flat.

Annivesaries

August, 29. the National Hero of Azerbaijan Chingiz Mustafaev's birthday
Papers "Ayna - Zerkalo" and "Adelet" are 6 years old
Teleprogram "Seher" is a year old

New Editions

   Paper "Alver" has come out on benalf of paper "Birja". The Chief Editor is
Mr. R Abbasov.
   International magazine " III era"  has started its life. Its creatoris Ramis
Mirov, the chief-editor is Aydin Balaev
   After a long break paper "Ulduz" restarted its publication
   After a two - year break "Azerbaijan Genjaleri" continued its work
   An informaion agency " Uluinform" started its activity. The Chief Executive
of the agency is Salim Babullaoglu.


"AVARSIA" STOPPED ITS PUBLISHIG, BUT ONLY TEMPORARY

    Lasted for a month time, debates and discussions resulted in cancellation of
executive organs' decision  to close down the Publishing House " Avarasia'.
Our aim is not to repeat all that has been written before but to provide you all
facts in chronological order to let you make your judgements on a basis of the
reason-aim-result principle.
    "Avrasia" was found in 1994.At first it was coming out once a week , but as its
editon rose in the beginning of 1996 it became a daily.In fact, according to the
survey carried out by the Journalists Union " Yeni nesil", "Avrasia" was
rated as third most popilar organ. The total edition of the 12- A-3-format-page
paper is 12,000 .
    01.08.96.
    The Media and Press Minister Mr.N.Hasan-zadeh sends a letter to the Director of
the Publishing House "Azerabaijan", in which he expresses his appeal to stop
publishing  "Avrasia". He motivates his decision by the "provocative
character"of some articles in the paper.
    02.08.96
    Today "Avrasia" does not  come out. From the meeting of the Chief Editor
Mr I.Sapmaz and MrN.Hasanzadeh it becomes known that the reason of paper's
close were materials published in recent issues. Among them there are articles
on the status of Russia's millitary base in Azerbaijan,Azerbaijan People's Front
Party's (APF) Deputy Leader Mr A.Karimov's press-conference, the killings of
Azerbaijani citizens in Russia, Azerbaiajn - Iran and Russia - Georgia relations.
    In the Journalists' Union's appeal they demand the fair and legal actions
regarding "Avrasia" and stressed that the Ministry was acting  against the
legilastion "About the information and Media Services". They also expressed
their solidarity with "Avrasia" collective.
    05.09.96
    Press services of the APFP  declare that it does not accept the close of
"Avrasia" and call for actions acordinly to the Legislation,"in other words only
the Court has right to shut any media or information agency"
    07.08.96.
    The Court of Yasamal district of Baku  recieves a leter-pretension from the
Midea and Information Ministry
    07.08.96
    The number of organisations,supporting " Avrasia",goes up. 5 more parties -
Musavat, Azerbaijan Democratic Party ( ADP ), Aerbaijan National Sovereignity
Party (ANSP) expressed their objectionaginst the close of the House and called
for resignation of Mr. N.Hasanzadeh.
    07.08.96
    The International Journalists Union's and "Reporters without borders"
organisation's General Director Mr. R. Menar in his letter to president Heydar
Aliyev expressed his thoughts regarding the close of "Avrasia".The letter says,
if the work the Publishing House is not restored then that will be most the
serious violation of the press freedom in Azerbaijan
    09.08.96.
    Press-cnferece is held at the "Avrasia"  head-quarters
Speaking about the reasons of the paper's close Mr I.Sapmaz  stresses that the
Media and Information Ministry is libelingthe House and notes that "Avrasia has
never concerned the national issues and never called for any kind of coup.
He also talks about the paper's finance. He says that one of it founders
"Bayragdar Holding" has withdrawed its paricipation.
    12.02.96
    The Court of Yasamal district of Baku starts hearing the case on "Avrasia"
close.The paper's solicitor Rustam Mehdiev presents the declaration of the paper's
management and informs that "Avrasia" stops its activity  and sending all its
staff off on holiday till the end of the trial. Then he reports that editor are
acting in such a way in order to heat up the tension in the air.After, he demands
to investigate the documents in which Censors ( Glavlit) and the Special Department
of the president's cabinet,in which they allowed "Avrasia" to publish the materials. In his turn, the
Ministry' solicitor Aleksander Goldman not agreeing with R.Mehdiev saysthis trial
is not about "... complete close of the paper, but a temporary  pause in
publishing". The trial is postponed till tomorrowto collect all necessary
documentation .
    13.08.96
    Due to A.Goldman's ilness the trial is put off for another day.
    14.08.96
    A.Goldman's health is not good enough to restart the trial.
    15.08.96
    The trial is postponed again and again because of illness of A.Goldman
    19.08.96.
    Doctor Rauf Aliyev reports that it might take long for A.Goldman to recover
Therefore, the trial is postponed for indefinite period of time.
    24.08.96
    After the meeting between Mr I.Sapmaz and Mr.A.Hasanov it becomes known that
"Avrasia" is allowed to restart its publishing from September,3. One of the
paper's executives says the President has agreed on this question.Meanwhile the
Chief Editor confesses that because of a lack of information supply not
always the state's interests have been taken into account.
    28.08.96
    Stop of the activity of "Avrasia" and longness of the trial sesult in the
internal conflicts. A group of journalists led by one of the editors Gafar
Chahmagli accuses the Chief Editor in making unforgivable mistakes and expresses
their inbelieve in his confidence. Chagmagli insists that if "Avrasia" is
allowed to be published then he will work only with new journalist team. And
eventually it becomes known about Chagmagli's appeal to the Media and Informaton
Ministry to isolate I.Sapmaz from the editorial duties and appointing Chagmagli
the chief editor.
    03.09.96.
    "Avrasia" under the management  by I.Sapmaz restarts its publication


CAUCUS: FREEDOM OF THE PRESS AND SPEECH

    Azerbaijan

    August,2. Article called "...Letters written in blood" in "Press-express"  is not
allowed to be published.It contains information about the attempted assasination
of president Heydar Aliyev and press-conference of three members
of the Azerbaijan People's Front Party suspected in the attempt and the party's
human rights commision's representatives.
    Augaust,8. The Court of Sabail district of Baku has strated  trial on the
Azerbaijan United Communist Party's(AUCP) appeal aginstthe Media and Information
Ministry regarding the registration  newspaper "Communist", founded by the party.On the
The representatives, presented at the Court as a third party, of the Azerbaijan
Communist Party(ACP) demanded to stop the trial,they motivating their demand
stated "Only ACP can found a newspaper called "Communist". In his turn, the
Media and Information Minister said, that a word 'communist' had changed its
meaning into 'tragedy' and he could not allow to publish a newspaper called with
this word. He also added that the fact that the property that was in use by
"Communist"  belonged to newspaper "Halg gaseti" and therefore the Ministry
would not register "Communist"
    August,8.The censors did not let "Azadlig" to publish their next issue. As the
editor in charge explained, they were punished for having included a poem in the
previous issue, that had been crossed out by the censors. The poem was on the
present situation in Nakhchivan.
    August,10. The censors forbade nawspaper "Muhalifat"  to publish an article on
human rights issues. Instead of the article four cartoons were published
    August,10 The political censors banned a publication of Aygun Muradhanli's
article on force authorities' despotism in the country.
    August, 15. The former Speaker Deputy ,Balash Abbaszadeh, a founder of paper
"Tanitim",despite of acute attack of diabetis, was send to the prison hospital.
Althogh his collegues, relatives and lawyers expressed their readiness to pay in
a bail, he was kept under arrest.
    August, 15. The censors banned a publication of material in "Azadlig". Instead
of the article a cartoon was published.
    August,21.The Court of Yasamal districtin Baku tried a trial regarding the
property dispute between the political commision of the Azerbaijan Democratic
Party and newspaper "Yeni Musavat".
    August,22.The censors banned an article in " Millet" on  corruption in
justice and state security authorities.
    August, 24. The censors banned an article in "Muhalifat"  about activity of
"Musavat" party.
    August,25.The Court of Yasamal district in Baku tried a trial on the claim of
the leader of the Azerbaijan Social Democratic Party Zardusht Alizadeh against
Firrudin Isaogli of newspaper "Nahchivan" regarding an article in the paper,
called "The Dishonest goes on about honesty". In the article Isaogli accused
Agazadeh in cooperating with Armenianins in Nagorny Karabakh.the court decided
that the claim was groundless. On this issue Agazaden said "I feel sorry for
the justice system which is based on corruption and unjustice.And this damages
the people believe in the government".
    August, 26. An article in "Azadlig" about the interview with the former head
of the Special Department in the president's cabinet Faig Rahimov was banned.
In the article he talked about  infregiments that had taken place in the work of
the Department and  the countries leaders'  disregard  to these infregiments.
    August,28.The censors banned two  articles in "Muhalifat" concernig the human
rights.
    August,31. An article in "Zerkalo" called "Elchibey's people movement" was
banned

    Armenia

    August 13-16.The Myaskanyan District Court tried a trial concerning the claim of
the director of Baking fabric 3 Mikail Martirosyan against the Chief Executive
of the Armenian National Radiocompany Stepan Zakaryan, the head of the Political
Department  of the company Gevorg Zakaryan, the chief editor of "Erevan" program
Vardan Vardanyan  regarding the reportage in the mentioned programe about the
Baking Fabric 3. In this program it was said about low product quality and under
weihgt of bread.The fabric director demanded an explanation for such a statement
The defendants reported that all information used in then program was taken from
the investigation carried out together with the Agriculture Ministry's
Information Service "Agropress".In the court resolution it was stated that they
refuted the charge though expressed their will  to apologize to Martirosyan.
After the court in the press-conference they declared that they would  take
the matter furhter to the Armenian High Court.According to the information
published by "izvestiya" , S.Zakaryan and ten reporters were sacked as well as
M. Martirosyan.THe president Ter-Petrosyan interfered in all this business,
"Izvestia" reported.

    Georgia

    August,1-5. The National Security Minister Shota Kviaria confirmed the rumours
that the assissanor of Russian journalist Vladimir Listiyev had been caught in
Georgia, the head of information center of the Ministry  David Tsentsadze
informed "Interfax". What is more RITA-SITA iinformed that the assassin had
been transformed to Russia
    Augast, 8. The Court  finished hearing the case regarding the claim of the
Executives of television channel " Rustavi-2" against the Post and Communication
Ministry.The Court's verdict banned the broadcasting on the chanel the programs
of advertising company "Gamma-Plus"
    August,13-15.The president Eduard  Shevarnadze said that the proceedings against
newspaper "Noe" had been instituted.The paper was accused of anti-semitism.He
also said:"I feel embarrassed that there are such newspapers in my country, the
country where Georgian and Jewish people have always lived and worked in peace".
The paper's Chief Editor Kivi Alaznaspireli was arrested in Tbilisi on August,15
after publishing article called "Be careful: there is a jew in front of you" in
his newspaper.

    Chechnya

    August,1-2. The press-secretary of the State Commision on Regulation of the
conflict in Chechnya Sergey Slipchenko in his interview to a reporter of RITA-TASS,
said that the reportages prepared by the ORT (Russian National Telecompany), TRT
(Russia's Tele- and Radiocompany) and NTR (Indepent Russian Telecompany} are
not objective.However, before leaving  for Chechnya,Sliplichenko refuted the ITAR-
TASS statement and said,"I was very surprised when I heard what I have never
said". Meanwhile the press secretary of the Chechen leader Ruslan Martagov,
merely repeated so "surprising" for Slipchenko  interview " Some media chanels
in a rush after a sensatrion exegarrate the real events"
    August, 2. "Reuter" reporter Dmitriy Kusnetz was detained at Artak town.
His comcorder was taken away.
    Augaust, 3 The Chief of the Russia's National Security Department Nikolay
Kovalev in his interview with a "Rossiskiye Novosti" reporter accused the leader
of chechen comondos Ruslan Hayhoraev in the killing of two journalist from
Petersburg: Maxim Shabalin and Felix Titov.
    August,6.The operators' group from NTV was taken under fire by the federal
soldiers near village Goyti
    August 6-15.During an attack of chechen army,a group of journalists representing
the  national press was blocked in a hotel in Grozhiy. The group consisted of :
ITAR-TASS reporters Andrey Hemelyanin, Andrey Klimov, Sergey Trofimov,reporter
of the Russian Information Agency (RIA) Vaciliy Dyachkov, ORT reporters
Konstatin Tochilin,Oleg Nikifirov, Mikhail Sothikov,RTR reporter Abren Baykov,
operator Yaroslavl Malishev and engineer Vladimir Seltcov,"Radio Rossiya"
reporter Vladimir Trushkovskiy and engineer Anatoliy Shushevich.Two days later,
the executives of agency "Interfax" made an appeal to the leaders of Russian and
Chechen armies to let the group out of the blocade. A number of the national
and internationa press and media organisations joined to the appeal.Among them:
"Radio Rossii" (radiocompany, Russia), "Guardian"(UK, newspaper), NTV(Russia,
telecompany), "Orient" (France, radiocompany), IRNA (Russia, information agency)
"Ekho Moskvi" (Russia, radiocompany), "Nepszabadzag" (Hungry, newspaper),
"Segodnya" ( Russia,newspaper), "trown" (Netherlands, newspaper), TANHUG
(Yugoslavia, information agency), "Borba"(Yugoslavia,newspaper), "La Unita"
(Italy, newspaper) "Vecherniy Sevastopol" (Russia, newspaper), TI (Hungry,
information agency), "Boston Globe" (Siria, newspaper), "Serebryaniy Dozhd"
(Russia, radiocompany) and the Slovakian National Radio. The Journalists
Protection Committee (USA)  distributed a press-release and president Boris
Eltsin and the head of Chechen head-quaters Aslan Maskhadov called for  the
journalists' release.On Augaust,11 the journalists were transformed to the
building of the National Security Department of Chechen Republic. On August,12,
two of them (Mikhail Sotnikov and Andrey Klinov) were released and and as ORT
reported they had videotapes recorded by they while they had been in the hotel.
On the same day the rest of the group was released too.On August, 15 , all 12
of them had  a press-conference in Moscow where they declared that both Russian
and Chechen army were keen on killing them.
    August,8 The WNA reporters' car was taken under the fire from the helicopters in
village Petropavlovskoe. There were  WNA producer Erad Faist, reporters Vakhtang
Sabshta, Sebastian Smith from "France Press", VLadmir Dolin from "EFE", Andrey
Babitskiy from "Svoboda" in the car.
The CNN car was taken under the fire from helicopters. In the car there were
the company's producer Steven Harrigan and operators Sergey Volkov, Vladimir
Ribalchenko.  The International Journalists Prorection Organisdation made an
appeal, in which the demanded adherence of the freedom of the press and speech
and gurauntee of journalists security in Chechenya.
     August,11. ORT reporter in Chechnya Ramzan Hagiev was killed near a Russian
observation post in Grozny.According to the information broadcasted on ORT next
day for last six days of Hagiev's life there had been no news from him. ORT
news services "Novosti" reported on August, 13 that the corpse was recognised in
the Tolstoy-Yurt village morgue by one of the Doku Zavgaev's bodyguards. The
telecompany also  supposed that the reporter was killed by the separatists.
However the car's driver who witnissed the killing ,testified that after having
passed the passport control at the control post and leaving the car was taken
under the fire from a Russian armoured vehicle.
    August,12. The Russia's Security Council Aleksandr Lebed on his return from
Chechenya, had an interview.Regardingthe work of the information services of the
Russian Ministry of Internal Affairs amd Ministry of Defence said "Udugov
(person, who critisized the work of the agencies) gets a top mark. That is the
one who works.But you are reproached with a incorrect and low-quality presentation
of the force authorities' work. But how can one be reproched if there is no any
kind of communication".
    August,13. The Publicity Protection Fund made an appeal, in wich the Russian
Prosecution organs were called for to investigate the facts of covering the
important information by the press .
    August, 14."Komsomolskaya Pravda" journalist Viktor Sokirko in his article
reports about an order given to the 166 engine-infantry brigade of Russian Army.
The brigade soldiers were ordered not to enter into conservation with the
pressmen.
    August,14.The Ministry of Internal Affairs of Russian Federation information
and public relations service together with the Ministry of Defence information
service announced that published in some newspapers articles suggesting
existence of contradiction between the Army and the Internal Troops are
groundless.
    August,14. RIA-"Novosti"  reported that The Ministry of Defence information
service had sent a group of its journalists to Chechnya in order to provide the
mass press with information.According to the announcement made by the Ministry
the group's objective is to provide the home and foreign press with important
information.In opinion of RIA-"Novosti"  such a move of the Ministry was caused
by recent critisism of its information service by Aleksandr Lebed.
    August,16. The Police executives of Perm oblast (province) forbade the
indepedent telechannel "Riphey" to broadcast a program prepared together with
the soldiers of the oblast special purpose police unit who had served in Chechnya.
    August,16.The Court of Timyrasovski district of Moscow started hearing the case
of NTV telecompany reporter Yelena Masyuk against newspaper "Shit i Mech" of the
Ministry of internal Affairs .In January in a newspaper's article,working then
in Chechnya  Masyuk was accussed in taking a bribe from the Chechen leaders for
interviewing Djokhar Dudaev and Shamil Basaev.In Masyuk's opinion
this mendacious information was spread by Moscow State University professor
Prokhorov.She demand apologies and publishing a denial.
Telecompany's representative Aleksandr Andreev said that only the author is
responsable for the article. The case hearing was postponed to September,23.
    August,19.On the intiative of weekly "Obshaya Gaseta", a commitee leading the
action of the biggest Russian newspapers against the war in Chechenya,was set up.
The committee leaders said that the urge to set such a comittee was caused by the
fact that "the press has run out of all other means of expressing their objection
against the war". The public and political figures joined the action.
    August,21.Lawyer Henri Reznic made an appeal in weekly "Obshaya Gazeta".In his
appeal he called for the journalists not to be so passive in presentation of the
case against publicist Valeria Novodvorskaya as they had been in the case
against "Moskovskiy Komsomlets" reporter  Vadim Poegli.
    Augaust,21.Addressing the Russian Federation Justice Chamber, the Chairman of
the National Bolshevist Party Eduard Limonov (Savenko) appealed to investigate
the reasons of "so big influence of the Information Minister of "so-called"
Chechen Republic Movladiy Udugov over Russian press ( "Otkritoe radio","Svoboda",
"Ekho Moskbi" radio stations,NTV telecompany)". In his appeal he also demanded
putting an end to "the use of the Russian radio by the Chechen thugs" and trying
a trial against radio station "Svoboda".
    August,28. The head of the National Security Council's press service Aleksandr
Barhatov accused some information organs in using the name of the Council in
presentation the information.According to the "Interfax" report , that
Barkhamatov thinks that  mendacious information is not  a result of the press's mad rush
after a sensation" but is a consequence of resistance of "some political circles
in Moscow" to the activity of A.Lebed in Chechnya.
    August, 28. The Chairman of Moscow "The Right to Live and Civil Dignity" rights
protection Organisation informed "Interfax" that two reporters - Vitaliy
Shevchenko and Andrey Bezavluk- working for independent telecompany "LITA-M"
 disappeared in Chechnya. They last were seen on August,9. UNA-UNCOreporte in
Ukraine Oleg Babiy in his interview with "Interfax-Ukraine" said the reporters
had taken part in negotitions on the exchange of captured by Chechens 12 Russian
soldiers with 7 Ukranian participants in a not-allowed demonstration in Minsk.
Thr Kharkov Freedom of the Press suggested that these journalisys were killed
by the Russian Security Council.
    August,30. Weekly "Zavtra"  in its 35th issue published article called "Russia-
the Motherland,Lebed - the betrator". in this artile NTV was interpretated as
the one that "covers the failure of Chechen campaign".In articles "Nina
Yetimova's compatriots -refugees from Chechnya" and "Tears of a wolve..."
NTV reporter Yelena Masyuk was interpretated as the who " is being fed from a
stranger's hand" and newspapers "Komsomolskaya Pravda" and "Mosko0vskiy
Komsomlets" as anti-Russian press.


MEDIA AS A MEAN OF "BRAIN WASHING"

    The poll carried out by one of the sociology services was to determine what
the readers of national press are interested in. Despite the fall of people's
real income the economic issues such as economy and business are in fifth
(21percent) and tenth (7,5 percent) places respectivevily. The political matters
most interesting for Azerbaijani readers - 57 percent  - are at the top of the
table:
   Theme                    Percentage
1.Politics                  57
2.War issiues               34,5
3.Entertainment             30,1
4.Foreign affairs           25
    The interest in politics demonstrates that the people are quite aware of the
the government's role in  illimination of any possible economic problems.
Therefore the government's attitude  to media is not surprising at all. The
governemnt realises that because of the censorship, a fall of peole's real
incomes ,a rise in prices  the only mean of getting information which can be
afforded by the population is radio and television. Moreover,it is established
that 97 percent of population still use home equipment which was produced in the
Soviet Union and unable to recieve FM waves And as a sequence,the private
telecompanies are allowed to  broadcast only on FM waves.
in freuqent mode.
    The example for what we said is the way the people were kept informed during the
parlaimentary elections: the censors' self willed activity against the canditates
from the opposition: the "sudden" electrycity cut when these canditates were on
TV.
    The EU Mass Media Institute was supervising the parlaimentary elections in
Russia,Georgia and Azerabijan.In general,the interpretation of election process
in Russia and Georgia met the requirement of the Institute. .But that can not be
said about Azerbaijan. The Institute representatives noted, that the press in
Azerbaijan for past two years had been under the pressure, set by the Government.
    How is the "brain washing" working in Azerbaijan?. According to the survey, only
13.6% of respondents believe in what they see on TV and read in the newspapers,
23.8% expressed thier partial believe in the mass media, and 34.5% reckon that
broadcasted information is trustworhless.It is a little to believe to the official
data  on the results of the elections reporting that more than two thirds supported
the perty in the power.In UN and ESCO represantatives noted that the international
requirements were not met during the election and election campaign in Azerabijan.
    In these conditions it is not surprising that 25-35% of the population is rather
to get information from the Russian television programs. Meanwhile 13 and 4,8 %
of the population are preferring to whatch first and second progams of Azerbaijan
television.Concernig the radio 30% expressed their preference to Russian "Mayak"
against only 8% who preffer the National Radio.
Eldar Zeynalov.
The director of the Azerbaijan
Human Rights institute

--------------------------
Source of given survey information : agencies "Express-sorgy", "Imidge" and
others.

